snippet.textDisplay: most plant based meat alternatives you can buy premade are less healthy.  many of them have higher fats and more calories per serving.  the only worthwhile alternative is lab grown meats with electrical stimulation.  plus plant alternatives is going to lead to more monocultures which predisposes our crops to plagues, which is curently happening with bananas.  If you want a decent plant based alternative you should make it yourself, check out sauce stache to see some recipes.  but im going to stick with eating meat (and not those with all the extra stickers to increase the cost with no proof of benefits).  All cattle is raised on pastures, some get added foods like grains and minerals and such, but all cattle sees grass.  When they are grass finished then they are allowed to get up to slaughter weight on grass alone while feedlot finished are fed grains and hay/straw (still grass).  If they were kept on feedlots their whole life they would become awfully ill and the whole herd would die quickly before coming close to slaughter.  Animals, specifically ruminants like cattle, turn unusable land into energy by breaking down cellulose and releasing more nutrient.  Plants also dont have all the essential nutrients that humans need.  There is a balance, we are omnivores so you need both or otherwise youll need lots of supplements.  An even better idea is mixing finely chopped mushrooms with your meat when you are making burgers, e\less calories per serving with added nutrients and helps you feel full faster.  So the meat lasts longer and you are eating healthier too.

If you want a decent plant based alternative you should make it yourself, check out sauce stache to see some recipes.  but im going to stick with eating meat (and not those with all the extra stickers to increase the cost with no proof of benefits).  All cattle is raised on pastures, some get added foods like grains and minerals and such, but all cattle sees grass.  When they are grass finished then they are allowed to get up to slaughter weight on grass alone while feedlot finished are fed grains and hay/straw (still grass).  If they were kept on feedlots their whole life they would become awfully ill and the whole herd would die quickly before coming close to slaughter.  Animals, specifically ruminants like cattle, turn unusable land into energy by breaking down cellulose and releasing more nutrient.  Plants also dont have all the essential nutrients that humans need.  There is a balance, we are omnivores so you need both or otherwise youll need lots of supplements.  An even better idea is mixing finely chopped mushrooms with your meat when you are making burgers, e\less calories per serving with added nutrients and helps you feel full faster.  So the meat lasts longer and you are eating healthier too.
